<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Neaadan Lupinespirit</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-12-28 16:23:54</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This is one of the most under-rated one hand slash weapons I've seen.  This weapon should easily sell for 2000 platinum pieces.  Before you scoff and agrue look at the stats.  9 damage, 25 delay  4 sv magic/fire/cold, Primary only.  Ok, now look at the Jagged Chokidai Spine.  SPINE not PROD.  9 damage 25 delay, 4 dex.  Piercer Primary/Secondary hand.  The spine sells for an average of 3000 platinum pieces.  There are only two reasons the razor should be a bit less, first is availability.  The Ebon Razor is a bit more common than the spine (for me 1 spine to 3 razor ratio).  Second is the fact that the spine is primary AND secondary.<BR>
<BR>
Now, my brother's level 40 ranger, whom I play from time to time, has a spine and a SSoY.  Most of the time I see him using the Spine in primary over the Yak..he says it does more damage than the Yak even with the proc.  Whenever I'm goofin with his toon I put the yak primary...just because I like the proc.<BR>
<BR>
On my warrior I use an Ebon Razor and dragoon dirk (I know...need to upgrade the offhand weapon) when I'm dual wielding.  With this kind of combination I never lose a bubble of stamina.  If I switch to these from my mithril two hander when stamina is low I can actually replenish stamina while fighting.<BR>
<BR>
Sorry for the long post but these are the facts as I have experienced them.  Take them as you will :)  Good luck and safe travels.</font></td></tr></table>
